<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1868-03-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1868-03-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="186" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d186">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Thornton</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Seward</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-03-23"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 23, 1868.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to transmit to you copy
                            of a dispatch addressed to Lord Stanley by Mr. Jorningham, her Majesty’s
                            chargé d’affaires <pb facs="0476" n="428" xml:id="pg_428"/> at Lima,
                            inclosing copy of a letter addressed to him by the United States consul
                            at Lambayeque, on the subject of the ill treament of two British
                            subjects by the revolutionary forces in North Peru, and I have been
                            instructed by his lordship to express to you the thanks of her Majesty’s
                            government for the friendly conduct of the United States consul in this
                            matter.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be, with the highest consideration, sir, your most
                            obedient, humble servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>EDWARD THORNTON.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>